Good evening, this is a very difficult time for everyone with so much uncertainty. As the situation continues to change rapidly, how we live our daily lives are also changing. We are all working so hard to adapt to so much change in such a short time, and I think you all are doing an amazing job transitioning your students from classroom to home school. Everyone is dealing with a great deal of emotions through this and so are our students, so I have created a facebook group to provide social and emotional tools as well as providing emotional support during this time. You can join anytime.
https://www.facebook.com/groups/631695937652552/

If you need extra support, please send me an email at Jenny.Duva@leonagroup.com

Thank you,
Jenny D'Uva

post_text:
Dear HPA Families, I have some wonderful news to share. The COVID-19 Food Group has 70 Blessing Bags to give out to our students. These bags are filled with all sorts of yummy snacks for your kiddos. They will be available for pick up on Tuesday, March 24th from 11 - 1, or until they run out.
We will be passing out the bags from the back of the school. Please enter the alley from Arapaho, driving towards Metrose Drive. Your driver side door will be closest to the school. Please do not get out of your car. You will be handed a bag and will be able to pull forward. Thank you & stay safe!

We will be passing out the bags from the back of the school. Please enter the alley from Arapaho, driving towards Metrose Drive. Your driver side door will be closest to the school. Please do not get out of your car. You will be handed a bag and will be able to pull forward. Thank you & stay safe!
